HeaderState

public HeaderState(boolean used,
                   java.lang.String name,
                   double startSampling,
                   double period,
                   ISBSIHeader header)
            throws SBSIParseException
DTO for the configuration of an FFT cost function that will use this state. Calling any of the set methods results in writing of the state data by the header file (to disk).

Parameters:
used - true if the cost function will use this state
name -
startSampling - time point at which the data for the state will start to be used
period - the periodicity of the data
header - SBSIheader which will persist the data in this DTO
Throws:
SBSIParseException
